Netsmart really looked to be
a leader in this space,
and we really looked to Amazon Q Developer

to lay the foundation for
what we were going to do in terms

of enhancing our software
development lifecycle processes.
Today we have about 150

of our engineers using Amazon
Q Developer for a variety

of automation tasks. So our
engineers can ask questions

to Q to help generate
code, to help ask questions

of code, to do code transformations,
to do code upgrades,
to do unit tests.

The documentation feature has
been helpful both

for our new engineers to quickly
onboard onto new projects,

but it's also good for Amazon Q to
continually learn our code base,

understand the solutions and the
markets that we're in

and help our engineers along
their development journeys.

By introducing Amazon Q
Developer into our engineering
processes, we really met AI

where our engineers work in
a day-to-day perspective.
They were able to communicate directly
with Amazon Q Developer
and Amazon Q have context into the
projects that they're working on.

And what that does is
it'll help streamline
what we can deliver,

and again, at a high
quality, high velocity rate,

where our engineers can
really focus in on innovation

and high-value tasks, rather
than repetitive tasks

that can require time and
and unnecessary effort.
